data.chText: 缺乏经验的；幼稚的；无知的；轻信的
data.enText: lacking experience of life, knowledge or good judgement and willing to believe that people always tell you the truth

data.chText: 真是难以相信你会幼稚到信任他！
data.enText: I can't believe you were so naive as to trust him!

data.chText: 他们对待生活的态度天真率直，令人耳目一新。
data.enText: Their approach to life is refreshingly naive.

data.chText: 稚拙派的（简单质朴，色彩明快）
data.enText: in a style which is deliberately very simple, often uses bright colours and is similar to that produced by a child

data.chText: 我天真地以为这活儿是有报酬的。
data.enText: I naively assumed that I would be paid for the work.

data.chText: 他们嘲笑他提的建议太幼稚。
data.enText: They laughed at the naivety of his suggestion.

data.chText: 她丝毫没有失去那份天真烂漫。
data.enText: She has lost none of her naivety.

simple_means.memory_skill: nai 出生 + ve → 刚出生的 → 幼稚的

means: 稚拙派的(简单质朴，色彩明快)

example: it seemed a bizarre ceremony to uninitiated western eyes
he took part in the experiment as a naive subject
lamentably unenlightened as to the laws

tr: of or created by one without formal training
example: primitive art such as that by Grandma Moses is often colorful and striking

tr: marked by or showing unaffected simplicity and lack of guile or worldly experience
example: a teenager's naive ignorance of life
the naive assumption that things can only get better
this naive simple creature with wide friendly eyes so eager to believe appearances

value.def: If you describe someone as naive, you think they lack experience and so expect things to be easy or people to be honest or kind.

example.ex: It's naive to think that teachers are always tolerant...
example.tran: 认为老师们总那么宽容是幼稚的。

example.ex: I must have been naive to think we would get my parents' blessing.
example.tran: 我一定太天真了，竟认为我们会得到我父母的祝福。

example.ex: Their view was that he had been politically naive.
example.tran: 他们认为他在政治上一直很幼稚。

gramarinfo.label: oft <l>it</l> v-link ADJ to-inf, ADJ to-inf

example.ex: ...naively applying Western solutions to Eastern problems...
example.tran: 幼稚地利用西方的办法解决东方的问题

example.ex: I thought, naively, that this would be a nine-to-five job.
example.tran: 我天真地以为这是份朝九晚五的工作。

example.ex: I was alarmed by his naivety and ignorance of international affairs.
example.tran: 他对国际事务缺乏经验且无知，这很让我吃惊。

partsOfSpeech.dec: cog〔= co 共同〕+ nat 出生 + e → 一同出生的 → 同种的
in 进入 + nat 出生 + e → 生来就带有的；自然产生的 → 生来的；天然的
nai 出生 + ve → 刚出生的 → 幼稚的
nasc 出生 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 出生的，新生的 → 初生的，萌芽的
nat 出生 + al …的 → 诞生的
natal 诞生的 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 出生率
nat 出生 + ion 表名词 → 出生之处 → 国家
nation 国家；民族 + ality 表性质 → 国民性；国籍
nat 出生 + ive …的 → 出生的地方 → 故乡的
nat 出生 + ure 行为，结果 → 出生就有的行为 → 天性
neo 新 + nat 出生 + e → 新生儿
re 一再 + nai 出生 + ss + ance 表情况 → 一再出生 → 复兴，新生
re 重新 + nasc 出生 + ent 具有…性质的，关于…的 → 再生的，复活的
